% \begin{align}
F(x,y) &= \dfrac{y\cdot\trma + x}{x\cdot \trma} \\ &= \dfrac{x \left[\frac{y}{x}\cdot \trma + 1 \right]}{x\cdot\trma} \\ &= \dfrac{\frac{y}{x}\trma + 1}{\trma} = g \left(\frac{y}{x} \right) \end{align} %text In other words, $F(x,y)$ is \underline\text{effectively} also a function of $\dfrac{y}{x}$. And this makes $F(x,y)$ a homogenous function%
